 Key Design Principles

 1. Reading-Optimized Width: 65ch max-width for prose content
 2. Generous Whitespace: 2-4rem spacing between sections
 3. Clear Hierarchy: Consistent heading scale (4xl → xl)
 4. Graph-Native Navigation: Leverage Neo4j relationships for context
 5. Server-Side Rendering: Markdown converted to HTML on server
 6. Mobile-First Responsive: Drawer on mobile, three-column on desktop
 7. Preserve What Works: Keep DaisyUI drawer, component architecture
 8. CSS-Only When Possible: Minimal JavaScript dependencies

 Performance Optimizations

 1. Markdown Caching: Cache rendered HTML by content hash
 2. TOC Generation: Generate once, cache with content
 3. Lazy Load Images: Native loading="lazy" on images
 4. Syntax Highlighting: Server-side with Pygments (fast)
 5. Neo4j Query Optimization: Single query for all graph nav data

 Testing Strategy

 1. Visual Regression: Compare typography rendering across pages
